code: combined_data <- nowcast_w_data |>   select(reference_date, initial_count, final_count) |>   distinct() |>   pivot_longer(     cols = c(initial_count, final_count),     names_to = "type",     values_to = "count"   ) |>   mutate(type = case_when(     type == "initial_count" ~ "Initially observed data",     type == "final_count" ~ "Final observed data"   )) |>   filter(reference_date >= nowcast_date - days(60))  nowcast_data_recent <- nowcast_w_data |>   filter(reference_date >= nowcast_date - days(60))  plot_prob_nowcast <- ggplot(nowcast_data_recent) +   geom_line(     aes(       x = reference_date, y = median     ),     color = "gray"   ) +   geom_ribbon(     aes(       x = reference_date,       ymin = q50th_lb, ymax = q50th_ub     ),     alpha = 0.5,     fill = "gray"   ) +   geom_ribbon(     aes(       x = reference_date,       ymin = q95th_lb, ymax = q95th_ub     ),     alpha = 0.5,     fill = "gray"   ) +   # Add observed data and final data once   geom_line(     data = combined_data,     aes(       x = reference_date,       y = count,       color = type     )   ) +   theme_bw() +   scale_color_manual(     values = c(       "Initially observed data" = "darkred",       "Final observed data" = "black"     ),     name = ""   ) +   xlab("Date of ED visit") +   ylab("Number of BAR cases") +   theme(legend.position = "bottom") +   ggtitle("Comparison of cases of BAR as of the nowcast date, later observed,\n and generated as a probabilistic nowcast") # nolint plot_prob_nowcast

title: Baseline nowcast for right-truncated epidemiological data
text: Nowcasting right-truncated epidemiological data critical timely public health decision-making, reporting delays can create misleading impressions declining trends recent data. package provides simple nowcasting methods practical use based using empirical delay distributions uncertainty past performance. also designed used baseline method developers new nowcasting methods. supports standard data frame inputs reference date, report date, count columns, compatible ‘epinowcast’ objects, also supports direct use reporting triangles. Alongside opinionated default workflow, low-level pipe-friendly modular interface, allowing context-specific workflows. can accommodate wide spectrum reporting schedules, including mixed patterns reference reporting (daily-weekly, weekly-daily). also supports sharing delay distributions uncertainty estimates strata, well custom uncertainty models delay estimation methods. details performance method(s) package applied case studies COVID-19 norovirus, see recent paper https://wellcomeopenresearch.org/articles/10-614/v1.

title: Create a dataframe of nowcast results from a dataframe of cases indexed by reference date and report date — baselinenowcast.data.frame
text: function ingests data.frame number incident cases indexed reference date report date one multiple strata, define unit single nowcast (e.g. age groups locations). returns data.frame containing nowcasts reference date strata, default estimated independently. function default estimate uncertainty using past retrospective nowcast errors generate probabilistic nowcasts, samples predictive distribution estimated final case count reference date. function implements full nowcasting workflow multiple reporting triangles, generating estimates delay uncertainty parameters strata using estimates across strata specified. estimate_delay() - Estimate delay PMF across strata strata_sharing contains "delay" estimate_uncertainty_retro() - Estimates uncertainty parameters across strata strata_sharing contains "uncertainty" as_reporting_triangle() - Generates reporting triangle object data.frame baselinenowcast.reporting_triangle() - Generates point probabilistic nowcasts depending output_type strata. @detail See documentation arguments function can used set model specifications (things like number reference times delay uncertainty estimation, observation model, etc.). function expects strata dataframe maximum delay. sharing estimates across strata, shared estimates made using shared set reference report dates across strata.

title: Create a dataframe of nowcast results from a dataframe of cases indexed by reference date and report date — baselinenowcast.data.frame
code: # S3 method for class 'data.frame' baselinenowcast(   data,   scale_factor = 3,   prop_delay = 0.5,   output_type = c("samples", "point"),   draws = 1000,   uncertainty_model = fit_by_horizon,   uncertainty_sampler = sample_nb,   max_delay = NULL,   delays_unit = "days",   strata_cols = NULL,   strata_sharing = "none",   preprocess = preprocess_negative_values,   ... )

title: Create a dataframe of nowcast results from a dataframe of cases indexed by reference date and report date — baselinenowcast.data.frame
text: data Data.frame long tidy format counts reference date report date one strata. Must contain following columns: - reference_date: Column type Date containing dates primary event occurrence. report_date: Column type Date containing dates report primary event. count: Column numeric integer indicating new confirmed counts pertaining reference report date. Additional columns indicating columns set unit single can included. user can specify columns strata_cols argument, otherwise assumed data contains data single strata. scale_factor Numeric value indicating multiplicative factor maximum delay used estimation delay uncertainty. Default 3. prop_delay Numeric value <1 indicating proportion reference times reporting triangle used delay estimation. Default 0.5. output_type Character string indicating whether output samples ("samples")estimate full uncertainty whether return point estimate ("point"). Default "samples". draws Integer indicating number probabilistic draws include output_type "samples". Default 1000. uncertainty_model Function ingests matrix observations matrix predictions returns vector can used apply uncertainty using error model. Default fit_by_horizon arguments obs matrix observations pred matrix predictions fits column (horizon) negative binomial observation model default. user can specify different fitting model replacing fit_model argument fit_by_horizon. uncertainty_sampler Function ingests vector matrix predictions vector uncertainty parameters generates draws observation model. Default sample_nb expects arguments pred vector predictions uncertainty parameters corresponding vector uncertainty parameters, draws negative binomial element vector. max_delay Maximum delay (units delays_unit) include nowcast. NULL (default), delays data used. specified, observations delay <= max_delay included. delays_unit Character string specifying temporal granularity delays. Options "days", "weeks", "months", "years". Default "days". strata_cols Vector character strings indicating names columns data determine stratify data nowcasting. unique combinations entries strata_cols denote unit single nowcast. Within strata, can repeated unique combinations reference dates report dates. Default NULL assumes data.frame passed represents single strata (one nowcast produced). columns part strata_cols removed. strata_sharing Vector character strings. Indicates estimates shared different nowcasting steps. Options "none" sharing (strata_cols fully independent), "delay" delay sharing "uncertainty" uncertainty sharing. "delay" "uncertainty" can passed time. preprocess Function apply reporting triangle estimation, NULL skip preprocessing. Default preprocess_negative_values(), handles negative values redistributing earlier delays. Set NULL want preserve negative values. Custom preprocess functions must accept validate parameter (defaults TRUE) enable validation optimisation internal function chains. ... Additional arguments passed estimate_uncertainty() sample_nowcast().

what: Create a dataframe of nowcast results from a single reporting triangle — baselinenowcast.reporting_triangle
title: Create a dataframe of nowcast results from a single reporting triangle — baselinenowcast.reporting_triangle
text: function ingests single reporting_triangle object generates nowcast form baselinenowcast_df object. function implements nowcasting workflow single reporting triangle: allocate_reference_times() - Allocate reference times used delay uncertainty estimation estimate_delay() - Estimate reporting delay PMF apply_delay() - Generate point nowcast using delay PMF estimate_and_apply_uncertainty() - Generate probabilistic nowcast point nowcast reporting triangle function default estimate delay reporting_triangle estimate uncertainty using past retrospective nowcast errors reporting_triangle generate probabilistic nowcasts, samples predictive distribution estimated final case count reference date. Alternatives include passing separate delay_pmf uncertainty_params. method specifically computes nowcast single reporting triangle. See documentation arguments function can used set model specifications (things like number reference times delay uncertainty estimation, observation model, etc.).

TRUE (default), validates object. Set FALSE called functions already validated. ... Additional arguments estimate_uncertainty() sample_prediction().

what: Estimate uncertainty parameters using retrospective nowcasts — estimate_uncertainty_retro
title: Estimate uncertainty parameters using retrospective nowcasts — estimate_uncertainty_retro
text: Estimates uncertainty parameters nowcasting creating series retrospective datasets input reporting triangle, generating point nowcasts datasets, calibrating uncertainty parameters based retrospective nowcast performance. function chains retrospective nowcasting workflow: truncate_to_rows() - Create retrospective snapshots apply_reporting_structures() - Generate retrospective reporting triangles estimate_and_apply_delays() - Generate point nowcasts estimate_uncertainty() - Estimate uncertainty parameters full probabilistic nowcasts (uncertainty estimation + sampling), use estimate_and_apply_uncertainty(). control individual steps (e.g., custom matrix preparation, alternative aggregation), use low-level functions directly.

code: # Generate point nowcast and uncertainty params from example data data_as_of <- syn_nssp_df[syn_nssp_df$report_date <= "2026-04-01", ] rep_tri <- as_reporting_triangle(data_as_of) |>   truncate_to_delay(max_delay = 5) |>   tail(n = 10) #> ℹ Using max_delay = 154 from data #> ℹ Truncating from max_delay = 154 to 5. point_nowcast_matrix <- estimate_and_apply_delay(rep_tri, n = 10) reporting_triangle <- apply_reporting_structure(rep_tri) uncertainty_params <- estimate_uncertainty_retro(   rep_tri,   n_history_delay = 8,   n_retrospective_nowcasts = 2 ) nowcast_draw <- sample_nowcast(   point_nowcast_matrix,   reporting_triangle,   uncertainty_params ) nowcast_draw #>            [,1] #>             472 #>             368 #>             534 #>             364 #>             459 #> 2026-03-28  400 #> 2026-03-29  605 #> 2026-03-30  442 #> 2026-03-31  366 #> 2026-04-01  471

text: Created package demonstration, made look like output preprocessing line-list data obtain number incidence cases specific syndromic surveillance definition, indexed date admission (reference date) date diagnoses reported surveillance system (report date) (e.g. reporting triangle long format).

what: A synthetic dataset resembling line-list (each row is a patient) data from the United States' National Syndromic Surveillance System (NSSP) accessed via the Essence platform. All entries are synthetic, formatted to look as close to the real raw data as possible. — syn_nssp_line_list

title: Truncate reporting_triangle to quantile-based maximum delay — truncate_to_quantile
code: data_as_of_df <- syn_nssp_df[syn_nssp_df$report_date <= "2026-04-01", ] # Create triangle, max_delay is automatically computed rep_tri <- suppressMessages(as_reporting_triangle(data = data_as_of_df))  # Check the maximum delay in the triangle ncol(rep_tri) #> [1] 155  # Truncate to 99th percentile of reporting rep_tri_trunc <- truncate_to_quantile(rep_tri, p = 0.99) #> ℹ Truncating to 136 based on 99% quantile. #> ℹ Truncating from max_delay = 154 to 136. ncol(rep_tri_trunc) #> [1] 137  # More aggressive truncation rep_tri_trunc90 <- truncate_to_quantile(rep_tri, p = 0.90) #> ℹ Truncating to 62 based on 90% quantile. #> ℹ Truncating from max_delay = 154 to 62. ncol(rep_tri_trunc90) #> [1] 63
